Founded in 1998, '''[http://www.kleiwerks.org Kleiwerks]''' is a US-based 501(c)3 international non-profit dedicated to teaching [[Natural building|Natural Building]]. We promote [[sustainable living]], social transformation and planetary healing through [[community]]-based people, projects and programs. Through our hands-on educational trainings and building projects with orphanages, schools, villages, [[permaculture]] sites and educational centers, we help generate regional networks of Natural Builders while creating public demonstration epicenters of sustainable living and ongoing service for in-need communities. We are part of a worldwide movement that is reviving and refining the art and joy of [[earthen construction|earthen]] and other indigenous [[building]] techniques.

